#. <section class="sutta" id="sn46.39"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn46.39:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 46"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 46"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn46.39:0.2"
msgid "4. Nīvaraṇavagga"
msgstr "4. Hindrances"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 39. Rukkhasutta → mahārukkhasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn46.39:0.3"
msgid "39. Rukkhasutta"
msgstr "39. Trees"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.39:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Santi, bhikkhave, mahārukkhā aṇubījā mahākāyā rukkhānaṃ ajjhāruhā, yehi "
"rukkhā ajjhārūḷhā obhaggavibhaggā vipatitā senti."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, there are large trees with tiny seeds and big trunks, which "
"grow up and around other trees as parasites. The trees they engulf break "
"apart, collapse, and fall."

#. VAR: vipatitā senti → senti. seyyathidaṃ (bj) | senti. seyyathīdaṃ (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "sn46.39:1.2"
msgid ""
"Katame ca te, bhikkhave, mahārukkhā aṇubījā mahākāyā rukkhānaṃ ajjhāruhā, "
"yehi rukkhā ajjhārūḷhā obhaggavibhaggā vipatitā senti?"
msgstr "And what are those large trees with tiny seeds and big trunks?"

# Kacchaka is so far as I know is unidentified. PTS dict says Cedrela Toona, but this is a mahogany. I name it in homage to my home, Sydney.
msgctxt "sn46.39:1.3"
msgid "Assattho, nigrodho, pilakkho, udumbaro, kacchako, kapitthano—"
msgstr ""
"The bodhi, banyan, wavy leaf fig, cluster fig, Moreton Bay fig, and wood "
"apple."

msgctxt "sn46.39:1.4"
msgid ""
"ime kho te, bhikkhave, mahārukkhā aṇubījā mahākāyā rukkhānaṃ ajjhāruhā, yehi "
"rukkhā ajjhārūḷhā obhaggavibhaggā vipatitā senti."
msgstr ""
"These are the large trees with tiny seeds and big trunks, which grow up and "
"around other trees as parasites. The trees they engulf break apart, "
"collapse, and fall."

msgctxt "sn46.39:1.5"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, idhekacco kulaputto yādisake kāme ohāya agārasmā "
"anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti, so tādisakehi kāmehi tato vā pāpiṭṭhatarehi "
"obhaggavibhaggo vipatito seti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, take some people from good families who have gone forth "
"from the lay life to homelessness, abandoning sensual pleasures. But beset "
"by sensual pleasures that are similar, or even worse, they break apart, "
"collapse, and fall."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.97"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.39:2.1"
msgid ""
"Pañcime, bhikkhave, āvaraṇā nīvaraṇā cetaso ajjhāruhā paññāya dubbalīkaraṇā."
msgstr ""
"There are these five obstacles and hindrances, parasites of the mind that "
"weaken wisdom."

msgctxt "sn46.39:2.2"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "sn46.39:2.3"
msgid ""
"Kāmacchando, bhikkhave, āvaraṇo nīvaraṇo cetaso ajjhāruho paññāya "
"dubbalīkaraṇo."
msgstr "Sensual desire,"

msgctxt "sn46.39:2.4"
msgid ""
"Byāpādo, bhikkhave, āvaraṇo nīvaraṇo cetaso ajjhāruho paññāya dubbalīkaraṇo."
msgstr "ill will,"

msgctxt "sn46.39:2.5"
msgid ""
"Thinamiddhaṃ, bhikkhave, āvaraṇaṃ nīvaraṇaṃ cetaso ajjhāruhaṃ paññāya "
"dubbalīkaraṇaṃ."
msgstr "dullness and drowsiness,"

msgctxt "sn46.39:2.6"
msgid ""
"Uddhaccakukkuccaṃ, bhikkhave, āvaraṇaṃ nīvaraṇaṃ cetaso ajjhāruhaṃ paññāya "
"dubbalīkaraṇaṃ."
msgstr "restlessness and remorse,"

msgctxt "sn46.39:2.7"
msgid ""
"Vicikicchā, bhikkhave, āvaraṇā nīvaraṇā cetaso ajjhāruhā paññāya "
"dubbalīkaraṇā."
msgstr "and doubt."

msgctxt "sn46.39:2.8"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca āvaraṇā nīvaraṇā cetaso ajjhāruhā paññāya "
"dubbalīkaraṇā."
msgstr ""
"These are the five obstacles and hindrances, parasites of the mind that "
"weaken wisdom."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.39:3.1"
msgid ""
"Sattime, bhikkhave, bojjhaṅgā anāvaraṇā anīvaraṇā cetaso anajjhāruhā bhāvitā "
"bahulīkatā vijjāvimuttiphalasacchikiriyāya saṃvattanti."
msgstr ""
"These seven awakening factors are not obstacles, hindrances, or parasites of "
"the mind. When developed and cultivated they lead to the realization of the "
"fruit of knowledge and freedom."

msgctxt "sn46.39:3.2"
msgid "Katame satta?"
msgstr "What seven?"

msgctxt "sn46.39:3.3"
msgid ""
"Satisambojjhaṅgo, bhikkhave, anāvaraṇo anīvaraṇo cetaso anajjhāruho bhāvito "
"bahulīkato vijjāvimuttiphalasacchikiriyāya saṃvattati … pe … "
"upekkhāsambojjhaṅgo, bhikkhave, anāvaraṇo anīvaraṇo cetaso anajjhāruho "
"bhāvito bahulīkato vijjāvimuttiphalasacchikiriyāya saṃvattati."
msgstr ""
"The awakening factors of mindfulness, investigation of principles, energy, "
"rapture, tranquility, immersion, and equanimity."

msgctxt "sn46.39:3.4"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, bhikkhave, satta bojjhaṅgā anāvaraṇā anīvaraṇā cetaso anajjhāruhā "
"bhāvitā bahulīkatā vijjāvimuttiphalasacchikiriyāya saṃvattantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"These seven awakening factors are not obstacles, hindrances, or parasites of "
"the mind. When developed and cultivated they lead to the realization of the "
"fruit of knowledge and freedom.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn46.39:3.5"
msgid "Navamaṃ."
msgstr ""
